SEOUL, Nov. 15 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Moon Jae-in's approval rating rose 3.1 percentage points over the week to 37.3 percent last week, a weekly poll showed Monday. The negative assessment on Moon's conduct of state affairs declined 4 percentage points to 58.9 percent, according to the Realmeter survey. Support for Moon's ruling Democratic Party gained 2.6 percentage points to 28.5 percent last week. The main conservative opposition People Power Party garnered 42.5 percent of approval score last week, down 3.5 percentage points from the previous week. The minor center-right People's Party won 8.5 percent of support, trailed by the minor center-left Open Democratic Party with 5.7 percent and the minor progressive Justice Party with 3.3 percent. The results were based on a survey of 2,522 voters conducted from last Monday to Friday. It had plus and minus 2 percentage points in margin of error with a 95 percent confidence level. Enditem